name: Landskrona Industrial and Agricultural Exhibition 1883
obverse: Bust of Oscar II facing right.
obverse_inscriptions: OSCAR II SVERIGES OCH NORGES KONUNG.
reverse: The coat of arms of Landskrona. Behind the coat of arms is a shovel, rake, scythe, and wheat.
reverse_inscriptions: MINNE AF LANTBRUKS OCH INDUSTRIUTSTÄLLNINGEN I LANDSKRONA
description: This medal was made to commemorate the industrial and agricultural exhibition held in Landskrona, Sweden in 1883.
